Title: [ANN][REVERSE ICO] AMO Coin - Blockchain for the ðŸš˜ CAR DATA ðŸš˜ Market
Body: Why did you choose reverse ICO rather than venture capital or angel investing?

Author: AMO_Official
Title: [ANN][REVERSE ICO] AMO Coin - Blockchain for the ðŸš˜ CAR DATA ðŸš˜ Market
Body: That's a great question! For a revolution to happen in the car data industry, we found that building a community and reaching big crowds is necessary in order to push change in attitude towards data ownership. This is supported by the concept of an ICO, as project participation is open to a much larger crowd than when working with more traditional financial institutions. Additionally, we believe that the decentralized nature of ICOs matches with our idea of utilizing blockchain technology to bring more horizontal control over data to the automobile industry. We believe that mainstream finance does not allow for a similar extent of transparency and shared ownership, and hence decided to go with an ICO to launch our new project!

Title: [ANN][REVERSE ICO] AMO Coin - Blockchain for the ðŸš˜ CAR DATA ðŸš˜ Market
Body: Announcement - Changes to ICO Schedule  Due to recent hacking incidents and security issues with major Korean cryptocurrency exchanges, we have received numerous reports from AMO ICO participants that they are unable to access their Ethereum nor make any transactions. We have contacted the exchanges to inquire when operations might resume, but according to their representatives nothing is certain for an indefinite period.  For this reason, AMO supporters have strongly requested a postponement to avoid any issues that they may encounter in participating in the ICO.  Therefore, AMO Labs has decided to delay our AMO Crowd Sale schedule by two weeks, with the sale set to start on July 14 at 9 a.m. (UTC +9).  * In case of changes in the exchange reopening schedule, further adjustments to the AMO ICO sale schedule may be announced at a later date. ** The sale will go on for seven days, beginning on July 14 at 9 a.m. (UTC +9) and ending on July 21 at 9 a.m. (UTC +9).  Despite this being an issue brought upon by external factors completely irrelevant to our project and team, we sincerely apologize for the abrupt announcement of changes to the sale schedule. Thank you for your continuous and generous support.

Body: Thank you for your feedback. We advice you to check our main website which has the identical information provided in our announcement. In regards to the 'reverse ICO,' this is a great question as the term 'reverse ICO' is a very exotic concept to most of us. Basically, the Reverse ICO is very similar with the traditional ICO(initial coin offering) in that both offer coins as incentives for the use of, or contribution to a service. However, the difference lies in the fact that the Reverse ICOs are used by established companies. It is basically a tool for established businesses to raise funds and get into cryptocurrency. These are companies with existing products and services and have real customers. The reverse part stems from the fact the company changes the business model from a centralized and fiat based to a decentralized and cryptocurrency based model. There are two significant benefits to this change. By using the Reverse ICO, you can raise more funds which can be used to revamp and expand the business. In addition, you can also decentralize your infrastructure with a cryptocurrency. That puts the company in a better position to be part of the new token economy. Furthermore, decentralizing threat intelligence and utilizing blockchain technology will be the future of cybersecurity.

Title: [ANN][REVERSE ICO] AMO Coin - Blockchain for the ðŸš˜ CAR DATA ðŸš˜ Market
Body: This is a good question that we receive a lot. In short, Reverse ICO is an ICO organized by an already established company. In other words, we're not a new startup created simply for the sake of holding an ICO. In our case, we have over 20 years of experience in the field, and most of the AMO team members are from the parent company of AMO, Penta Security Systems. The biggest reason why most ICOs fail is due to lack of hands-on experience and especially lack of financing knowledge. For us, these are not an issue. When joining Reverse ICO projects, you can be sure to get involved in companies that have roots, legacy, and expertise, which is extremely important in the ICO field.

Title: [ANN][REVERSE ICO] AMO Coin - Blockchain for the ðŸš˜ CAR DATA ðŸš˜ Market
Body: This is a great question as the term 'reverse ICO' is a very exotic concept to most of us. Basically, the Reverse ICO is very similar with the traditional ICO(initial coin offering) in that both offer coins as incentives for the use of, or contribution to a service. However, the difference lies in the fact that the Reverse ICOs are used by established companies. It is basically a tool for established businesses to raise funds and get into cryptocurrency. These are companies with existing products and services and have real customers. The reverse part stems from the fact the company changes the business model from a centralized and fiat based to a decentralized and cryptocurrency based model. There are two significant benefits to this change. By using the Reverse ICO, you can raise more funds which can be used to revamp and expand the business. In addition, you can also decentralize your infrastructure with a cryptocurrency. That puts the company in a better position to be part of the new token economy. Furthermore, decentralizing threat intelligence and utilizing blockchain technology will be the future of cybersecurity.
